<F P=101> CORPORATE ALLIANCES </F>
<H3> <TI>   Aerospatiale, DASA To Join Matra-Bae Missiles </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94WS0205B Paris AIR &amp; COSMOS/AVIATION MAGAZINE INTERNATIONAL 
in French 17-23 Jan 94 p 11 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> 94WS0205B </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AIR &amp; COSMOS/AVIATION MAGAZINE INTERNATIONAL 
in French 17-23 Jan 94 p 11 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>French </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [Article by P.L.: "1994: Year of Merger Among European </F>
Missile Manufacturers"; introductory paragraph in boldface as 
published] 
  [Text] Both teams are making preparations 
simultaneously for French-British and French-German 
regroupings--which are then expected to merge. 
  Discussing the merger of missile activities by Matra Defense 
and British Aerospace [BAe] Dynamics, Noel Forgeard, 
Matra-Hachette's general manager in charge of defense and space 
and chief executive officer of Matra Defense, writes in the 
group's in-house newspaper that "detailed talks between the 
teams are making progress, with both sides showing a desire to 
conclude the discussions as soon as possible in 1994." 
  According to Forgeard, "it is very desirable that the 
resulting Matra-BAe (missile) company be joined by Aerospatiale 
and Deutsche Aerospace [DASA], and it is very likely that that 
will happen in the medium term." 
  For the time being, the French-German team is continuing its 
separate efforts to merge the missile activities of those two 
firms in a new company that may be called Euromissile, thus 
retaining the name of the current consortium. But this is not 
certain, since the two companies have asked for in-house 
suggestions regarding a less "Euro" name! 
  What is certain, on the other hand, is that the merger of 
missile activities by Aerospatiale and Deutsche Aerospace is in 
the final stretch. Officials met in Munich before Christmas to 
finalize their communication strategy with a view to an upcoming 
announcement regarding the new French-German missile company 
formed by Aerospatiale and DASA. 
  It is therefore likely that we will see the simultaneous 
regrouping of Matra-BAe and Aerospatiale and DASA in 1994. 

</TEXT>

