<H3> <TI>   France: Marketing Shapes Cisi Software Latest Restructuring </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94WS0228B Paris 01 INFORMATIQUE in French 14 Jan 94 p 8 -- 
FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> 94WS0228B </F>
<F P=104>  Paris 01 INFORMATIQUE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [Article: "Cisi Regroups Its Subsidiaries"] </F>
  [Text] SSII, a subsidiary of CEA-Industries and Cap Gemini 
Sogeti, is supposed to finalize its reorganization by this 20 
January. According to a company spokesperson, Cisi is getting 
rid of a structure defined on the basis of tasks and is 
preparing to restructure its organization on the basis of its 
customers' market sectors. As a result, Cisi Ingenierie, Cisi 
Transtec and Cisi Telematique (excluding the part that is being 
reattached to Athesa France, Cisi's and Bull's joint subsidiary 
in facilities management) are going to merge into a single 
company. That will depend on Cisi SA, the financial holding 
company that is supposed to head up the group's overseas 
subsidiaries, as well as Athesa France. This restructuring is 
supposed to impart dynamism to Cisi activity (FF70 million in 
losses in 1992 on a turnover of FF1.5 billion) and accelerate 
structural savings. Shuffling the workforce at Rungis is also on 
the agenda. 

</TEXT>

