<H3> <TI>   Mitsubishi Motors Selling Electric Vehicle </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94P60111 Tokyo NIKKAN SANGYO SHIMBUN in Japanese 26 Jan 94 p 
12--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> 94P60111 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo NIKKAN SANGYO SHIMBUN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:CSO 

  [Text] Mitsubishi Motors Corp. began selling its Libero EV 
electric vehicle on 25 January. Selling at the high price of 
&yen;11.23 million, the company plans for sales to government 
agencies and large corporations. Three vehicles are already 
said to have been ordered by the [Tokyo] Minato District office. 
Mitsubishi Motors is aiming for annual sales of 50 vehicles. 
  The Libero EV is based on the ``Libero Cargo 1500G.'' 
Mitsubishi Motors and Tokyo Electric Power Co. converted it 
into an electric vehicle. Mitsubishi Motors is the first 
company to sell the bonnet-wagon type of electric vehicle. On a 
single charge, the vehicle is capable of travelling 165 
kilometers at a constant speed of 40 kilometers per hour. 

</TEXT>

