<H3> <TI>   Sumitomo Lab To Conduct Micromachine R&amp;D </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94P60108 Tokyo NIKKAN KOGYO SHIMBUN in Japanese p 9--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> 94P60108 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo NIKKAN KOGYO SHIMBUN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:CSO 

  [Text] Sumitomo Electric Industries Ltd. (Noritaka 
Kurauchi, president) held a ceremony opening its Haruma 
Laboratory built at the Haruma Science City in western Hyogo 
Prefecture. The laboratory, with its superconducting, 
small-scale ``NIJI-III'' SOR (synchrotron orbit radiation) 
device, will conduct R&amp;D on precision machining for 
micromachines as well as such topics as new materials and 
funtionally gradient materials. The laboratory is built on a 
two-hectacre industrial site (in Kamigori, Hyogo Prefecture) 
obtained from Hyogo Prefecture. The total cost of building the 
lab came to &yen;5 billion. 

