<F P=100> Nuclear Engineering </F>
<H3> <TI>   Construction of Demonstration ATR To Be Delayed One Year </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94FE0172C Tokyo NIKKEI SANGYO SHIMBUN in Japanese 17 Nov 93 
p 5 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> 94FE0172C </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo NIKKEI SANGYO SHIMBUN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:CSO 

  [Text] The construction plan for the new demonstration ATR 
that the Electric Power Development Company is building at Oma 
City, Aomori Prefecture, will be postponed about one year. The 
Demonstration ATR Construction Promotion Committee comprised of 
representatives from the electric power industry, MITI, STA, 
etc., will make its decision in the near future. The 
construction plan that will be presented to the Electric Power 
Development Coordination Council in December 1994 will call for 
construction to begin in April 1997 and operation to begin in 
2003. 
  The plan has been delayed by lengthy negotiations over 
compensation with the local fishermen's union, but the Oma 
Fishermen's Association decided to accept the prefecture's 
mediation concerning additional fishing industry compensation, 
so it is possible that negotiations will finally move forward 
once again. 
  This is the seventh postponement since the Promotion 
Committee first hammered out the demonstration ATR construction 
process in 1985. 

</TEXT>

