<F P=100> Nuclear Engineering </F>
<H3> <TI>   PNC Starts Adjustment Operation of ATR Fugen </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94FE0171D Tokyo KAGAKU KOGYO NIPPO in Japanese 15 Nov 93 p 
16 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> 94FE0171D </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KAGAKU KOGYO NIPPO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:CSO 

  [Text] PNC, which has been conducting the 11th periodic 
inspection of the ATR Fugen nuclear power plant reactor 
(prototype reactor, rated output 165,000 kW) since 18 August, 
restarted the reactor and achieved criticality on 14 November. 
Today PNC will begin adjustment operation, which is the final 
stage of the periodic inspection process. Engineers will check 
out plant performance as they slowly increase output, and they 
plan to return to full operation after the government's final 
inspection in the middle of December. 
  In this periodic inspection, engineers inspected the reactor 
facility, turbine equipment and electrical equipment, and they 
confirmed there were no abnormalities. 

</TEXT>

